abstract: Ronald S. Lauder, the Estée Lauder heir, offered himself up as back-channel negotiator to purchase Greenland from Denmark, a new book says. Denmark said no.
snippet: Ronald S. Lauder, the Estée Lauder heir, offered himself up as back-channel negotiator to purchase Greenland from Denmark, a new book says. Denmark said no.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — One of the odder moments of Donald J. Trump’s presidency came when he publicly floated the idea of buying Greenland. It caused a predictable furor, generated gales of late-night television jokes and soured relations with Denmark, which rejected the idea of selling the giant Arctic territory.

main: Cosmetics Billionaire Convinced Trump That the U.S. Should Buy Greenland
print_headline: Cosmetics Billionaire Convinced Trump the U.S. Should Buy Greenland

abstract: Researchers at Carnegie Mellon University developed an A.I.-powered arm that can paint an abstract acrylic. Is it art?
snippet: Researchers at Carnegie Mellon University developed an A.I.-powered arm that can paint an abstract acrylic. Is it art?
lead_paragraph: One day recently, on a table in Jean Oh’s lab in the Squirrel Hill neighborhood of Pittsburgh, a robot arm was busy at a canvas. Slowly, as if the air were viscous, it dipped a brush into a pool of light gray paint on a palette, swung around and stroked the canvas, leaving an inch-long mark amid a cluster of other brushstrokes. Then it pulled back and paused, as if to assess its work.

main: This Robot Can Paint. But Is It Art?
print_headline: Building a Machine With an Artistic Side
